<section os="linux" id="sec.rpminst">
  <title>Installation from RPMs</title>

  <para>Two SCIRun <firstterm>Problem Solving Environment</firstterm>s
  (<acronym>PSE</acronym>), BioPSE and Fusion, are available via
  RPMs. RPMs are available for each supported Linux distribution.
  Customized SCIRun <acronym>PSE</acronym>s can be built from source
  code, see <xref linkend="sec.source_inst"/></para>

  <para>The BioPSE RPM includes SCIRun packages BioPSE,
  MatlabInterface, Teem, and Insight.  The BioPSE RPM includes ITK
  libraries required by the Insight package.  Matlab software must be
  present to use modules of the MatlabInterface package.</para>

  <para>The Fusion RPM includes SCIRun packages Fusion, DataIO, and
  Teem.  The Fusion RPM includes the HDF5 libraries.  The
  SCIRun/Fusion RPM has been built to use MDSplus software but MDSplus
  software must be installed separately.  See <xref
  linkend="sec.mdsplus_inst"/> for MDSplus software installation
  instructions.</para>

  <para>The version of SCIRun included in all RPMs has been configured
  to support BLAS but BLAS libraries must be installed separately.
  See <xref linkend="sec.blas_lapack_inst"/> for BLAS installation
  instructions (BLAS/ATLAS and LAPACK are often pre-installed in Linux
  distributions).</para>

  <para>Root privileges are required to install the SCIRun
  <acronym>RPM</acronym>s.  SCIRun is installed in
  <filename>/usr/local/SCIRun/bin</filename>.</para>

  <para>
    Follow these steps to install SCIRun:
    <orderedlist>
      <listitem>
	<para><link linkend="sec.rpm_download">Download</link> a
	SCIRun RPM distribution, documentation, and sample data
	sets.</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
	<para><link linkend="sec.rpm_install">Install</link> SCIRun
	using the <command>rpm</command> command.</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
	<para><link linkend="sec.rpm_data">Install</link> SCIRun's
	sample data sets.</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
	<para><link linkend="sec.rpm_docs">Install</link> SCIRun's
	documentation.</para>
      </listitem>
    </orderedlist>
  </para>

  <para>Be sure to read <xref linkend="sec.prepare" /> after
  installing, but before starting, SCIRun.</para>

  <section id="sec.rpm_download">
    <title>Downloading</title>
    <para>
      From <acronym>SCI</acronym>'s <ulink
      url="http://software.sci.utah.edu/archive_entry.html">software
      archive</ulink> page download the following files:
      <itemizedlist>
	<listitem>
	  <para>
	    <filename>SCIRunBioPSE-<!--%= doc.version
	    %-->-<replaceable>system</replaceable>.rpm</filename> or
	    <filename>SCIRunFusion-<!--%= doc.version
	    %-->-<replaceable>system</replaceable>.rpm</filename>
	  </para>
	  <para>Above, <replaceable>system</replaceable> is the Linux
	  system of interest.</para>
	</listitem>
	<listitem>
	  <para>
	    <filename>SCIRunData.1.24.0b_to_1.24.1.tar.gz</filename>
	    if updating an existing
	    <filename>SCIRunData/1.24.0b</filename> directory.
	  </para>
	  <para>
	    <filename>SCIRunData.<!--%= doc.version
	    %-->.tar.gz</filename>, which contains all datasets for
	    SCIRun <!--%= doc.version %-->.
	  </para>
	  <para>
	    <filename>FusionData.<!--%= doc.version
	    %-->.tar.gz</filename> for Fusion users.
	  </para>
	</listitem>
	<listitem>
	  <para>
	    <filename>SCIRunDocs.<!--%= doc.version %-->.tar.gz</filename>
	  </para>
	</listitem>
      </itemizedlist>
    </para>

  </section>

  <section id="sec.rpm_install">
    <title>Installing</title>
    <para>
      The following procedure installs SCIRun in directory
      <filename>/usr/local/SCIRun</filename>.  After intallation is complete,
      commands for starting SCIRun and its PowerApps can be found in
      <filename>/usr/local/SCIRun/bin</filename>
      (<filename>/usr/local/SCIRun/bin/scirun</filename>,
      <filename>/usr/local/SCIRun/bin/BioImage, etc.</filename>)
    </para>
    <para>
      Use the <command>su</command> command to become the root user.
      Then <command>cd</command> to the directory containing the
      SCIRun RPM and type:
      <literallayout class="monospaced">
rpm -ivh SCIRun-<!--%= doc.version %-->-<replaceable>system</replaceable>.rpm
      </literallayout>
    </para>
    <para>The RPM should take approximately one minute to
    install.</para>
    <para>
      Type <command>exit</command> to leave the root account.
    </para>
    <para>
      SCIRun can be removed using the <command>rpm</command> command:
      <literallayout class="monospaced">
rpm -e SCIRun
      </literallayout>
      Read  <xref
      linkend="sec.prepare"/> before
      <link linkend="sec.starting">starting</link> SCIRun.
    </para>
  </section>

  <section id="sec.rpm_data">
    <title>SCIRun's Sample Data Sets</title>
    <para>
      The following instructions install the sample data sets into
      <filename>/usr/local/SCIRunData/<!--%= doc.version
      %--></filename>.
    </para>
    <para>
      Use the <command>su</command> command to become the root user.  Then
      <command>cd</command> to the directory containing the 
      dataset tarball and:
      <itemizedlist>
	<listitem>
	  <para>
	    If installing
	    <filename>SCIRunData.1.24.0b_to_1.24.1.tar.gz</filename>
	    type:
	    <literallayout class="monospaced">
mv /usr/local/SCIRunData/1.24.0b /usr/local/SCIRunData/1.24.1
tar -x -z -f SCIRunData.1.24.0b_to_1.24.1.tar.gz -C /usr/local
	    </literallayout>
	  </para>
	</listitem>
	<listitem>
	  <para>
	    If installing <filename>SCIRunData.<!--%= doc.version
	    %-->.tar.gz</filename> type:
	    <literallayout class="monospaced">
tar -x -z -f SCIRunData.<!--%= doc.version %-->.tar.gz -C /usr/local
	    </literallayout>
	  </para>
	</listitem>
	<listitem>
	  <para>
	    If installing <filename>FusionData.<!--%= doc.version
	    %-->.tar.gz</filename> type:
	    <literallayout class="monospaced">
tar -x -z -f FusionData.<!--%= doc.version %-->.tar.gz -C /usr/local
	    </literallayout>
	  </para>
	</listitem>
      </itemizedlist>
      Type <command>exit</command> to leave the root account.
    </para>
  </section>

  <section id="sec.rpm_docs">
    <title>SCIRun's Documentation</title>
    <para>
      The following procedure installs the documentation
      in the directory <filename>/usr/local</filename>
    </para>
    <para>
      Use the <command>su</command> command to become the root user.  Then
      <command>cd</command> to the directory containing the compressed
      documentation tarball and type:
      <literallayout class="monospaced">
tar -x -z -f SCIRunDocs.<!--%= doc.version %-->.tar.gz -C /usr/local
      </literallayout>
      This will create <filename>/usr/local/SCIRunDocs.<!--%= doc.version %--></filename> (the
      SCIRun documentation directory). Type <command>exit</command> to leave the
      root account.
    </para>
    <para>
      Open <filename>/usr/local/SCIRunDocs.<!--%= doc.version %-->/doc/index.html</filename>
      with a web browser to view SCIRun's online documentation.
    </para>
  </section>

</section>
